  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Design4Jobs</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">For young unemployed South Africans poverty levels are high and a lack of basic skills can make it hard for them to find work and change their situation. Job creating enterprises within South Africa have been established, manufacturing products under the fair trade model and distributing predominately to a domestic market. However, with limited access to wider international retailers, the market is limited. This project aims to address this by engaging the expertise of high value retail brands to provide a robust distribution channel and communicate consumer needs to South African manufacturers. This will help to build the capacity of local enterprise, design, manufacturing and marketing organisations to support craft businesses and producers to meet the requirements of the international and local markets. They will also provide basic skills and enterprise training to unemployed young people seeking to enter the sector. This will increase the knowledge and sales volumes of the micro enterprises, creating more jobs and decent income, thereby moving more people out of poverty.</narrative>
  </description>
